{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":5634,"text":"Do I look real to you?"},{"time":8133,"text":"Hope so."},{"time":9797,"text":"I have no idea if you're seeing this,"},{"time":11624,"text":"but I'm just going to look ahead\nand trust that you're there."},{"time":15802,"text":"I've drawn a semicircle\nin the sand in front of me"},{"time":18590,"text":"so I don't walk past it\nand look like I'm floating in midair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26433,"text":"Right now I'm standing"},{"time":29132,"text":"in the open air,"},{"time":30307,"text":"on a beach under a palm tree,"},{"time":33949,"text":"in the exact spot\nwhere your stage used to be."},{"time":38160,"text":"I have 12 minutes with you."},{"time":40581,"text":"I set a limit."},{"time":42850,"text":"My wife Navid once said"},{"time":44029,"text":"that infinite possibility\nis a creator's worst enemy."},{"time":48633,"text":"For example, this dress: I'd asked\nher to design something"},{"time":51534,"text":"that a priest might have worn\nin 23rd-century Cairo."},{"time":54911,"text":"But we only had three days to make it,"},{"time":57967,"text":"and the only fabric we had"},{"time":59695,"text":"was an old duvet cover\nthat another resident left behind."},{"time":62440,"text":"But she did it, and it's perfect."},{"time":67010,"text":"And she looked at it and said,"},{"time":69664,"text":"\"Proof of concept --\ncreation needs constraint.\""},{"time":75727,"text":"So with these 12 minutes,"},{"time":79072,"text":"I'm going to tell you\nabout my greatest discovery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84812,"text":"For my whole life, my obsession\nhas been eternal life,"},{"time":89256,"text":"as I know it is so many of yours."},{"time":93848,"text":"You may be happy to know\nthat your research will pay off."},{"time":98160,"text":"I am 318 years old."},{"time":101486,"text":"The average human lifespan\nis now 432 years,"},{"time":105281,"text":"and my work has been to extend\nthe human lifespan indefinitely."},{"time":109363,"text":"And I've never questioned that someday,"},{"time":111874,"text":"we'll reach a point\nwhere we'll be content."},{"time":116959,"text":"But the opposite keeps happening:"},{"time":118589,"text":"the longer we live,\nthe longer we want to live,"},{"time":121087,"text":"the less we want to die."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123974,"text":"Who can blame us?"},{"time":126183,"text":"The universe is so big."},{"time":130548,"text":"There won't ever not be more to see."},{"time":132478,"text":"Just yesterday,"},{"time":133653,"text":"I was reading about how you can\ntake out a boat on Europa"},{"time":136437,"text":"and sail from island to island\nall over the planet,"},{"time":138875,"text":"and some of the islands have villages\nthat you can stay and visit"},{"time":142132,"text":"and sleep under the shadow of Jupiter."},{"time":144945,"text":"And then there's this other island\nwhere there's just one songwriter"},{"time":149016,"text":"who sits and plays mandolin for the ocean."},{"time":151517,"text":"And then there are others\nwhere there's no one"},{"time":154456,"text":"and there never has been,"},{"time":155886,"text":"and so you go just for the pleasure\nof touching your foot to sand"},{"time":159735,"text":"that no foot has ever touched before."},{"time":163309,"text":"You could spend 400 years doing just that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171627,"text":"Right now the Moon is rising\nin the Northeast."},{"time":175013,"text":"I can see the cities on it\nwith my naked eye."},{"time":177188,"text":"They're connected like nerve clusters:"},{"time":180332,"text":"Mariapolis on the South Pole,\nand Ramachandran on the Equator."},{"time":186956,"text":"And New Tehran in the Sea of Tranquility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192334,"text":"That's where Navid and I met."},{"time":194472,"text":"We were both artists downtown."},{"time":198138,"text":"The day we met, we were passing\neach other in Azadi Square,"},{"time":201018,"text":"and we bumped shoulders."},{"time":202504,"text":"And I turned to apologize"},{"time":204279,"text":"and she, without saying hello\nor introducing herself or anything,"},{"time":208602,"text":"said, \"Well, why do you think\nwe didn't just pass through each other?\""},{"time":214101,"text":"And first of all, I thought,\n\"Who the hell are you?\""},{"time":218363,"text":"But second, the question annoyed me,"},{"time":220409,"text":"because the answer is so simple."},{"time":222898,"text":"I said, \"We didn't pass through each other"},{"time":225332,"text":"because elementary particles have mass"},{"time":227600,"text":"and because the space\nbetween elementary particles"},{"time":229997,"text":"is filled with the binding energy\nthat also has the properties of mass,"},{"time":233393,"text":"and we've known that for 800 years.\""},{"time":237919,"text":"She must have been in one of those moods"},{"time":239899,"text":"where she likes to mess with strangers."},{"time":241811,"text":"Or maybe she was just flirting with me,"},{"time":243724,"text":"because she looked at me and said,\n\"I thought you'd say that."},{"time":248636,"text":"Think deeper.\""},{"time":249811,"text":"And then she took off her belt,"},{"time":251358,"text":"this belt that I'm wearing now,"},{"time":256408,"text":"and she said,"},{"time":260607,"text":"\"Our universe is built\nso that particles have mass."},{"time":266769,"text":"Without that basic constraint,"},{"time":268294,"text":"we'd have just passed right through\neach other at the speed of light"},{"time":271801,"text":"and never even known.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":276239,"text":"And that's how our romance began."},{"time":286128,"text":"Navid and I"},{"time":289239,"text":"never ran out of things to talk about."},{"time":293310,"text":"Never."},{"time":295100,"text":"It was incredible."},{"time":296276,"text":"It was like we were both heroes\nclimbing up into a mountain range together"},{"time":300834,"text":"and we kept arriving at new vistas,"},{"time":303313,"text":"and these new, perfect\nconstellations of words"},{"time":306333,"text":"would come out of us to describe them."},{"time":308214,"text":"And we'd forget them\nas soon as we made them,"},{"time":310362,"text":"and throw them over our shoulder\nand go on to the next thing, on and up."},{"time":313807,"text":"Or one time, Navid said that our talk\nwas like we were always making bread,"},{"time":317745,"text":"and that we were always\nadding in a little more flour"},{"time":321288,"text":"and a little more water,"},{"time":322761,"text":"and folding it in and turning it over"},{"time":324738,"text":"and never getting around to baking it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332589,"text":"If my obsession was eternal life,\nNavid's obsession was touch."},{"time":338772,"text":"She had a genius for it."},{"time":341502,"text":"All of her work revolved around it."},{"time":345383,"text":"My body was like a canvas for her,"},{"time":347613,"text":"and she would draw her fingertip\ndown over my face so slowly"},{"time":352258,"text":"that I couldn't feel it moving."},{"time":354265,"text":"And she was obsessed with the exact moment"},{"time":356962,"text":"when I would stop being able to tell\nthe difference between her body and mine."},{"time":363721,"text":"Or she would just lie across me\nand dig her shoulder into mine"},{"time":366740,"text":"and say, \"Pilar, why does\nthis feel so good?\""},{"time":371009,"text":"I'd say, \"I don't know!\""},{"time":375640,"text":"And she always had a facetious answer\nfor her facetious question,"},{"time":381033,"text":"but the answer I remember today is,"},{"time":385399,"text":"\"It feels good"},{"time":386574,"text":"because the universe chose\nits constraints,"},{"time":389378,"text":"and we are its art.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":401677,"text":"It's always funny what you think\nthe future is going to be like"},{"time":404726,"text":"versus what it turns out to be."},{"time":408169,"text":"In your time, scientists thought\nhumans could freeze themselves"},{"time":411297,"text":"and wake up in the future."},{"time":413761,"text":"And they did -- but then they died."},{"time":419083,"text":"In your time, scientists thought\nhumans could replace organs"},{"time":422867,"text":"and extend life for hundreds of years."},{"time":426311,"text":"And they did,"},{"time":427681,"text":"but eventually, they died anyway."},{"time":431381,"text":"In your time, Earth\nis the only place people live."},{"time":437826,"text":"In my time, Earth is the place\npeople come to die."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445539,"text":"So when Navid started to show the signs,"},{"time":449083,"text":"our friends assumed I would do\nwhat everyone does,"},{"time":451539,"text":"which is say goodbye\nand send her to Earth,"},{"time":454517,"text":"so that none of us\nwould have to look at her"},{"time":457756,"text":"or be around her\nor think about her and her ..."},{"time":462225,"text":"failure to keep living."},{"time":468811,"text":"More than anything,"},{"time":470019,"text":"they didn't want to be around\nher actual physical body."},{"time":472820,"text":"They kept referring to it as \"declining,\""},{"time":476536,"text":"even though she herself\nwas fascinated by it,"},{"time":478825,"text":"the changes it was going through,"},{"time":480972,"text":"following the rules of its nature\nday by day, independent of her will."},{"time":488481,"text":"I did send Navid to Earth."},{"time":491948,"text":"But I came with her."},{"time":494600,"text":"I remember a friend of ours,\njust before we left, said,"},{"time":498192,"text":"\"I just think it's arrogant,"},{"time":501080,"text":"like the rules don't apply to you,\nlike you think your love is that special.\""},{"time":507497,"text":"But I did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512468,"text":"So, even here on Earth,"},{"time":513882,"text":"I kept working on how to extend life."},{"time":517198,"text":"It didn't occur to me"},{"time":518373,"text":"that there could be any other response."},{"time":520440,"text":"I kept going back to that thing\nthat Navid said to me"},{"time":523003,"text":"that day in Azadi Square,"},{"time":524766,"text":"that without that basic constraint --"},{"time":527486,"text":"a universe that granted mass to matter --"},{"time":529786,"text":"we would not exist."},{"time":533481,"text":"That's one rule."},{"time":534676,"text":"Another rule is that all mass\nis subject to entropy."},{"time":539929,"text":"And there is no way to be\nin this universe without mass."},{"time":542724,"text":"I know. I tried everything."},{"time":544430,"text":"I tried creating a photon box\nwhere the Higgs field was altered."},{"time":549043,"text":"I tried recording all\nsubatomic movements in my body"},{"time":553199,"text":"and replaying them on closed loop."},{"time":555010,"text":"Nothing worked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561184,"text":"But my final innovation\nwas to create a coil dimension"},{"time":566968,"text":"with the boundaries of a body\nin which time moved infinitely slower,"},{"time":572635,"text":"but whose projection would appear\nto move in normal time."},{"time":577400,"text":"That body would then appear\nin our universe as a hologram --"},{"time":583215,"text":"here but not here."},{"time":589166,"text":"When I realized I'd done it,"},{"time":591987,"text":"I ran to her room,"},{"time":593867,"text":"so happy to tell her I'd done it,"},{"time":596838,"text":"moving through space\nalmost normally to all eyes,"},{"time":600366,"text":"even to my own,"},{"time":603950,"text":"and went to lie down next to her,"},{"time":607262,"text":"and forgot, and fell right through her."},{"time":616303,"text":"I'd found a way to eternal life,"},{"time":620448,"text":"at the expense of the one thing\nNavid loved most,"},{"time":622782,"text":"which was to touch and be touched."},{"time":629939,"text":"And she threw me out."},{"time":636420,"text":"I still got to watch, though."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639748,"text":"Humans live 400 years now,"},{"time":641504,"text":"and we still die."},{"time":642906,"text":"And when death comes,"},{"time":646342,"text":"the dying still pick at their bedsheets,"},{"time":652319,"text":"and their arms break out\nin blue and violet blooms on the insides,"},{"time":656154,"text":"and their breaths get further\nand further apart,"},{"time":659692,"text":"like they're falling asleep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669780,"text":"I've always thought that"},{"time":671796,"text":"what gives a life meaning is adventure."},{"time":675476,"text":"And death is just a problem"},{"time":677893,"text":"we haven't discovered the solution to yet."},{"time":684594,"text":"But maybe a life has meaning\nonly because it ends."},{"time":688221,"text":"Maybe that's the paradox:"},{"time":689568,"text":"constraints don't constrain,\nthey allow perfect freedom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699175,"text":"(Sighs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":705963,"text":"There was a thunderstorm\nhere this morning."},{"time":708011,"text":"There is another forecast for tonight,"},{"time":709868,"text":"but for now the sky is clear."},{"time":712937,"text":"I can't feel the wind here,"},{"time":714314,"text":"but I just asked one of the caretakers\nwho passed by what it felt like,"},{"time":717702,"text":"and she said it felt warm,\nlike melted butter."},{"time":723464,"text":"An answer worthy of my wife."},{"time":730861,"text":"I have to find my way back to the flesh."},{"time":736980,"text":"Until then, I take up no space\nbut the space you give me."}]}]}